### Description
The **Create Layout (BD) **task allows to select and configure ITX templates for the creation of document layouts.

### Configuration
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

- In the **Alias **field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- In the **Templates Project &gt; Project &gt; Resource **field, select the [Document Templates](/doxee-platform/docs/document-templates-resource-reference) resource to be used.

- In the **Templates **section, configure rulesets for selecting the ITX template(s) to be used:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Reference file**: Upload a generic XML file as the reference data schema.

> File size limit

The maximum upload size for the reference file is **100KB**. Its recommended to use the smallest possible structure, as large reference files might degrade respositivity and performance.

- **Document selector**: Select an element of the data schema which contains the document identifier from the drop-down menu.

- *(optional) ***Template selector**: Select the attribute (if any exists) which identifies the ITX template.

- Click **Add **to add and configure a new rule:

**Rule**: Enter an alias for the rule.

- **Selector value**: Enter the document or template selector value which shall trigger the rule.

- **Template file**: Select the ITX template to be used for the triggered rule.

- In the **Output management &gt; Project &gt; Resource **field, select the [Output Management](/doxee-platform/docs/output-management-resource-reference) resource to be used.

- *(optional) *Toggle the **Relaxed mode **to omit validation error notifications.

- In the **Pattern **field, enter the name of the input file or a filename pattern (for example, **.xml*).

- In the **Images **field, select the method to retrieve external images. The available options are:

**Predefined**: The image path is inside the default path.

- **Dynamic**: The image path is in the output of a previous task in the workflow. Select the path from the drop-down menu.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- **Custom**: From a shared volume, specifying the last part of the filesystem path (for example: */MyDCProject*) where the images are previously loaded.
